{"v":1,"id":"qj9yjKjDPQ5Dgk4l1XVT","createdAt":"2026-06-21T19:09:21.152Z","app":{"name":"AxiVale","version":"1.2.0"},"kind":"conversation","title":"Compare all the players who have played Reaper across all available runs. Use only metrics from time logged on Reaper. Compare only players who are members of FAFO guild. Prioritize Downs Contribution > Strips > Damage to Downs > Chill > Vulnerability. Player downs and deaths count as minimum negative. Minimum Sample of 2 runs per player. Created a table with weighted results","turns":[{"userText":"Compare all the players who have played Reaper across all available runs. Use only metrics from time logged on Reaper. Compare only players who are members of FAFO guild. Prioritize Downs Contribution > Strips > Damage to Downs > Chill > Vulnerability. Player downs and deaths count as minimum negative. Minimum Sample of 2 runs per player. Created a table with weighted results","agentText":"\n\nI'll kick off parallel lookups — guild membership, available runs, and where each metric lives in AxiBridge — all at once.\n\nGood. Now I'll pull the FAFO guild roster, examine the AxiBridge rollup for Reaper-specific data, and check if per-condition (Chill/Vuln) data is available.\n\nKey finding: the rollup's combat metrics are all null for profession-filtered rows. I need to dig into per-run summaries and also confirm the conditions breakdown. Let me probe the summary structure and pull player stats in parallel.\n\nNow let me look at the per-player structure inside a run summary, so I can write the right jq aggregation query.\n\nThe summary player object has `downContribution`, `downsCaused`, `strips`, `deaths`, `downs` (own downs). Now let me query all 29 runs, extract per-player rows only where profession == \"Reaper\", filter to FAFO accounts, and aggregate. I'll also pull the per-run conditions_out section to check if Chill/Vuln are broken out.\n\nAll the data I need is in. Now let me compute the weighted scores. Conditions_out shows all zeros across the dataset — Chill and Vulnerability are not captured in AxiBridge, so those two metrics will be flagged and excluded. Let me work through the full weighted calculation.\n\n---\n\n**Data collected (Reaper-only runs, FAFO members, ≥2 Reaper runs — 29 runs total, Apr 24 – Jun 17 2026):**\n\nFirst I normalize each player's **per-combat-hour** rate to a 0→1 score within the pool (0 = worst, 1 = best). Penalties (self-downs, deaths) are inverted — 0 = least penalized, 1 = most penalized.\n\n**Score formula:**\n> **Score = 5 × DC_norm + 4 × Strips_norm + 3 × DTD_norm − 1 × SelfDown_pen − 1 × Death_pen**\n>\n> Max achievable: **12.0** (all positive metrics at pool-best, zero downs/deaths)\n\n---\n\n## FAFO Reaper Comparison — Weighted Results\n\n*All rates are per Reaper combat hour. Chill & Vulnerability excluded — AxiBridge `conditions_out` returned no data (all zeros); when available, max score expands to /15.0. Score is out of 12.0.*\n\n| **#** | **Player** | **Reapr<br>Runs** | **Cmbt<br>hr** | **Downs/hr**<br>×5 | **Strips/hr**<br>×4 | **DC Dmg/hr**<br>×3 | **Self↓/hr**<br>−1 | **Deaths/hr**<br>−1 | **Score<br>/12.0** |\n|:---:|:---|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|\n| 🥇 | **iNicooo.9587** | 7 | 5.4 | **61.4** | 1,552 | **1,425k** | 8.3 | 5.7 | **10.61** |\n| 🥈 | **Athena.4562** | 9 | 5.7 | 45.0 | **1,780** | 1,156k | 11.9 | 5.1 | **8.84** |\n| 🥉 | **FatherHyperion.1047** | 6 | 5.8 | 51.6 | 1,595 | 824k | **4.0** | **2.9** | **8.46** |\n| 4 | Hostile Pudding.5617 | 11 | 8.7 | 51.8 | 1,474 | 1,217k | 12.6 | 6.7 | **8.34** |\n| 5 | Blades Of Fatalis.1279 | 4 | 2.6 | 48.4 | 779 | 1,288k | 19.9 | 13.7 | **4.38** |\n| 6 | Siren.9741 | 5 | 4.9 | 39.4 | 1,054 | 733k | 10.5 | 6.2 | **4.08** |\n| 7 | brittikaye.6159 | 13 | 6.8 | 25.3 | 953 | 576k | 17.3 | 9.1 | **1.09** |\n| 8 | Endless.4325 | 9 | 7.4 | 26.4 | 777 | 578k | 18.9 | 12.6 | **0.10** |\n| 9 | Kurayamino.9738 | 5 | 4.2 | 14.4 | 858 | 403k | 22.9 | 13.5 | **−1.66** |\n\n**Bold values** = pool best in that column (lowest for penalties).\n\n---\n\n### Score breakdown per player\n\n| Player | DC (×5) | Strips (×4) | DTD (×3) | Self↓ (−1) | Deaths (−1) | **Total** |\n|:---|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|\n| iNicooo | 5.00 | 3.09 | 3.00 | −0.23 | −0.26 | **10.61** |\n| Athena | 3.26 | 4.00 | 2.21 | −0.42 | −0.20 | **8.84** |\n| FatherHyperion | 3.96 | 3.26 | 1.24 | 0.00 | 0.00 | **8.46** |\n| Hostile Pudding | 3.98 | 2.78 | 2.39 | −0.46 | −0.35 | **8.34** |\n| Blades | 3.62 | 0.00 | 2.60 | −0.84 | −1.00 | **4.38** |\n| Siren | 2.66 | 1.10 | 0.97 | −0.34 | −0.31 | **4.08** |\n| brittikaye | 1.16 | 0.70 | 0.51 | −0.70 | −0.57 | **1.09** |\n| Endless | 1.28 | 0.00 | 0.51 | −0.79 | −0.90 | **0.10** |\n| Kurayamino | 0.00 | 0.32 | 0.00 | −1.00 | −0.98 | **−1.66** |\n\n---\n\n### Key takeaways\n\n1. **iNicooo.9587 (#1, 10.61)** dominates the two highest-weight metrics — best downs/hr AND best damage-to-downs/hr in the pool. High upside on every positive metric; penalty drag is well-controlled for a multi-profession player (only 7 of 15 total runs on Reaper).\n\n2. **Athena.4562 (#2, 8.84)** owns the strips throne (1,780/hr — 12% above #2). Her penalty footprint is also low. The one gap vs. iNicooo is downs/hr (45 vs. 61).\n\n3. **FatherHyperion.1047 (#3, 8.46)** is the durability outlier — lowest self-downs *and* lowest deaths per hour in the pool (penalties are literally zero), which lifts him to 3rd despite middle-of-pack damage-to-downs. Note: only 6 Reaper sessions — smallest sample at the top.\n\n4. **Hostile Pudding.5617 (#4, 8.34)** is the volume anchor — most Reaper runs (11), very high absolute totals. Scores almost identically to FatherHyperion except penalties eat ~0.8 pts.\n\n5. **Blades (#5)** has elite damage-to-downs (2nd in pool) but crippling penalty drag (13.7 deaths/hr, 19.9 self-downs/hr) and zero strip rate — only 4 sample runs.\n\n6. **brittikaye (#7) and Endless (#8)** both suffer from high penalty rates relative to their output. Endless is a 100% Reaper main (only profession across all 9 runs), making this a clean readout — survivability is the limiting factor.\n\n7. **Kurayamino (#9, −1.66)** is the only player in negative territory: lowest downs/hr, lowest damage-to-downs, AND highest self-down + death rates. High-priority coaching target.\n\n> ⚠️ **Chill & Vulnerability data unavailable** — `conditions_out` returned zero values across all runs in this dataset. Those two metrics (priority 4 & 5, weights 2+1) are excluded. When AxiBridge begins capturing per-condition output, re-run this comparison; scores and rankings may shift, especially for players running heavy chill builds.","filedAt":"12:15 PM","tools":[{"name":"gw2_account_info"},{"name":"axibridge_runs_list"},{"name":"axibridge_find","display":{"kind":"table","data":{"title":"Sections for \"down contribution damage to downs\"","columns":[{"key":"section","label":"Section"},{"key":"title","label":"What"},{"key":"granularities","label":"Granularity"}],"rows":[{"section":"damage_taken","title":"Damage taken","granularities":"player, squad"},{"section":"strips","title":"Boon strips","granularities":"player, squad"},{"section":"down_contribution","title":"Down contribution","granularities":"player, squad"},{"section":"crowd_control","title":"Crowd control (received)","granularities":"player, squad"},{"section":"boons","title":"Boon generation","granularities":"player, category, squad"},{"section":"damage_mitigation","title":"Damage mitigation","granularities":"player, squad"},{"section":"healing","title":"Healing output","granularities":"player, category, squad"},{"section":"barrier","title":"Barrier","granularities":"player, squad"}]}}},{"name":"axibridge_find","display":{"kind":"table","data":{"title":"Sections for \"chill vulnerability conditions applied\"","columns":[{"key":"section","label":"Section"},{"key":"title","label":"What"},{"key":"granularities","label":"Granularity"}],"rows":[{"section":"conditions_out","title":"Ou